# Project-level npm registry override.
#
# Why this exists (v1.25.1 Phase E): the maintainer's ~/.npmrc sets
# registry=https://registry.npmmirror.com (China mirror). When running
# `npm install` locally without an explicit --registry flag, npm picks
# up ~/.npmrc and writes the mirror URL into package-lock.json's
# "resolved" fields. Obsidian CI runs `npm install` on Linux with the
# default official registry; CI's lockfile resolution then produces a
# main.js with a different hash than the local release asset, triggering
# the "Build output does not match the released main.js artifact"
# warning that demotes the release score.
#
# Pinning this project to registry.npmjs.org locally keeps both lockfile
# trees consistent. This file overrides ~/.npmrc per-project (npm reads
# the project .npmrc first, then user config).
registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
